This is my 1st experience eating from this restaurant. I choose it becuz it was black owned. So I support black businesses✊🏾.I ordered through the Uber Eats app becuz of Covid-19.  So I ordered the chicken sandwich with BBQ sauce and seasoned curly fries. So I'm not going to completely act as if I'm completely upset becuz I don't know who's fault it is. Yet, I will say I am a little disappointed with how things turned out. So Uber Eats have it labeled as chicken sandwich. So what is not know is fried or grilled. It's FRIED and with CHEESE for those who do not know. On Uber eats it does not clarify that. Google menu also might not have this on the menu at all. So there is no telling that it's served that way or not. As for the seasoned fries, it's a small amount, like just a real hand full and underwhelming.  Overall it wasn't a bad experience, but I think something needs to be done about those issues with clarifying exactly how certain food are being served. The food tasted good despite my displeasure with it being fried chicken sandwich with cheese on it without knowing. Now that I know I would order again with much more confidence.

It may look small but had to the back and it opens up! There's two bars on in the front and one in the back. The music the DJs played where good. The food isn't over priced but they do charge taxes on the food. I had brought two orders of wings and curly fries at $6 a piece, which should have been $18 but I paid $20.89 cause of taxes. They even sell seafood like crab legs! I only had one drink which costed me $6 and there's was no tax on the drink. They charge $3 for a bottle of water or you can get a free cup of water from a pitcher they keep in the refrigerator with the the Beer and sodas. There is room to dance on the floor between the tables against the wall and the bar. I am not a regular customer, in fact this was my first time going there. But do I think that this spot is great for either a quick bite and drink or to hold a celebration or small crowed party. Don't know how f I myself will be back due to how far I live away (Bronx), but it's seems like a great neighborhood hangout.
